Version 1 Rules
The Test System exists only for development.
It may be completely disabled in release builds.
It never contains gameplay logic.
It never owns gameplay state.
Every gameplay action is delegated to the appropriate manager.
It never bypasses manager responsibilities.
It may depend on all managers and utilities.
Managers must never depend on the Test System.
DeveloperMenu is the only entry point for developer tools.
TestController routes all developer commands.
DebugCommands never implement gameplay; they only invoke manager APIs.
DebugOverlay is read-only and displays runtime information.
PerformanceProfiler only measures runtime performance.
ValidationTools performs consistency checks without changing game state.
TestScenarioRunner automates sequences of manager API calls for testing.
The subsystem should be removable without requiring changes to gameplay systems.